===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|𢇍|斤|t1=to cut|t2=axe|ls=ic}}.

Before the Qin dynasty, this character was written as {{zh-l|𠸿}} or {{zh-l|𠜷}}. According to ''{{w|Shuowen}}'', the left component is an old form of {{zh-l|*叀}}.

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*dan|t=to cut}}. Compare {{cog|lus|tan|t=to cut}} (STEDT).

